Resolve establishing a commission to consider the inclusion of nuclear energy in Massachusetts'
future energy planning.
1 Resolved, (a) There shall be a special Commission to study the advantages and
2 advisability of including nuclear power generation in future planning for the energy needs of the
3 Commonwealth. The commission shall investigate: (1) the distinct benefits accruing from the
4 inclusion of nuclear power in the generation portfolio for Massachusetts, (2) challenges and risks
5 involved in nuclear power generation, (3) economics of nuclear power generation, and (4)
6 comparison of nuclear energy to other available energy sources with respect to reliability and
7 environmental impact, including the costs or benefits of not including nuclear power generation
8 in Massachusettsâ€™ energy portfolio.
9 (b) The Commission shall consist of 15 members, including 1 member appointed by the
10 Senate President, who shall serve as co-chair; 1 member appointed by the Speaker of the House
11 of Representatives, who shall serve as co-chair; 2 members to be appointed by the Governor, one
12 of whom shall be the Secretary of Environmental Affairs or a designee, the executive director of
13 ISO-NE or a designee, the chairman of the board of the Massachusetts Municipal Wholesale
